Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on scheduling jobs on a shared cluster to maximize resource utilization and improve the quality of machine learning models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper deals with training machine learning models and improving their quality. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as machine learning is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a scheduling system for distributed machine learning, which involves managing resources and optimizing performance. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with training machine learning models, which often involve neural networks.
